  <amendments/>
  <summary>6/23/1999--Introduced.
Increases from 50 to 100 percent the amount of gain excluded from the sale of certain small business stock. Reduces from five to three years the holding period applicable to such a sale. Makes such exclusion available to corporations. Makes the stock of larger businesses eligible.Repeals the minimum tax preference for the exclusion for incentive stock options.</summary>
